Apparently stack.top is not a singleton!  This was breaking our caching behavior because we were creating a new Client on each request  effectively negating all caching benefits :(  This commit fixes the issue by moving our client / application singletons onto the app itself.

Fix splitting in configuration.py  I hit a (very corner case!) bug where a configuration variable (in my case the database password) contained a '=' character  which broke the parsing at that line with the error:  'too many values to unpack'  Changing from split('=') to split('=' 1) will ensure that the splitting only happens on the *first* '=' which is what is intended.

fix a blocking issue in the spout caused by emitting multiple messages in next tuple in a while loop that caused the acking mechanism to get starved (as it operates on the same thread). As a fix we will emit a fixed number of messages. That number will be determined by the prefetch count configured for the spout as that limit emitting to messages that were already prefetched.
